al Discourse and Public Image of the Spanish Scouts (1912–1931 -- tContributors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume discusses a broad range of themes and methodological issues around images, photography and film. It is about sharing a fascination about the visual history of education and how images became the most influential (circulating) media within the field of education on local, regional, national and international levels. Within this volume images are primarily analyzed as presenters, mediators, and means of observation. Images are seen as mobile reproducible media which play an active role within the public and educational sphere. They are means of observation and storytelling, they shape identities by presenting models of how we should act in and perceive the world, they circulate though different contexts and media, all of which impacts their meanings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aFilm. 4aFotografie. 4aIdentitätsbildung. 4aMeinungsbildung. 7aHISTORY / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aIdentity formation.  aMovie.  aOpinion forming.  aPhotography.1 aBarceló Bauzà, Gabriel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraster, Sjaak, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aComas Rubí, Francisca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aComas Rubí, Francisca, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFullana Puigserver, Pere, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGelabert Gual, Llorenç, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález Gómez, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález Gómez, Sara, eeditor.4edt4http://id